<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Home Church — The Life of David</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&family=Source+Serif+Pro:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #ffffff;
    --ink: #111111;
    --ink-2: #2a2a2a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
    --faint: #9a9a9a;
    --line: #e8e8e8;
    --line-2: #f1f1f1;
    --gold: #D3BC8D;        /* Saints Old Gold */
    --gold-deep: #b39966;
    --gold-soft: #f5efe1;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  html, body { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.6;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    font-size: 16px;
  }
  .serif { font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', Georgia, serif; }

  /* ===== Header ===== */
  header.site {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 1.25rem 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: .75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  h1.title {
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    margin: 0 0 .5rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -.5px;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .subtitle {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: .98rem;
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    max-width: 480px;
  }
  .gold-rule {
    width: 56px;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--gold);
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
  }
  .progress-wrap { max-width: 420px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .progress-text {
    font-size: .82rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: .45rem;
    letter-spacing: .3px;
  }
  .progress-text strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 600; }
  .progress-bar {
    background: var(--line-2);
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 99px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .progress-fill {
    background: var(--gold);
    height: 100%;
    width: 0%;
    transition: width .5s ease;
  }

  main {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.25rem 4rem;
  }

  /* ===== Controls ===== */
  .controls {
    display: flex;
    gap: .5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }
  .controls button {
    background: #fff;
    color: var(--ink);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: .55rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: .85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all .15s;
    letter-spacing: .2px;
  }
  .controls button:hover {
    border-color: var(--ink);
    background: #fafafa;
  }
  .controls button.primary {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: #fff;
    border-color: var(--ink);
  }
  .controls button.primary:hover { background: #333; }
  .controls button.ghost {
    border-color: transparent;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .controls button.ghost:hover { color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--line); }
  .controls .spacer { flex: 1; }

  /* ===== Week ===== */
  .week {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: border-color .15s;
  }
  .week:hover { border-color: #d8d8d8; }
  .week-header {
    padding: 1.1rem 1.4rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    user-select: none;
    transition: background .12s;
  }
  .week-header:hover { background: #fafafa; }
  .week.open .week-header {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .week-meta { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }
  .week-number {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: .7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 2.5px;
    color: var(--gold-deep);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: .15rem;
  }
  .week-title {
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', serif;
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.2;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -.2px;
  }
  .week-progress {
    font-size: .82rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
  .chevron {
    color: var(--faint);
    transition: transform .2s, color .15s;
    font-size: .85rem;
  }
  .week:hover .chevron { color: var(--ink); }
  .week.open .chevron { transform: rotate(90deg); color: var(--gold-deep); }
  .week-body { display: none; }
  .week.open .week-body { display: block; }

  /* ===== Day ===== */
  .day {
    padding: 1.5rem 1.4rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-2);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr auto;
    gap: 1.1rem;
    align-items: start;
  }
  .day:first-child { border-top: none; }
  .day.complete { background: #fcfaf5; }
  .day.today {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #fdfaf2 0%, #fff 100%);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
    padding-left: calc(1.4rem - 3px);
  }

  .day-num {
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: .9rem;
    background: #fff;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    transition: all .15s;
  }
  .day.complete .day-num {
    background: var(--gold);
    border-color: var(--gold);
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .day.today .day-num {
    background: var(--ink);
    border-color: var(--ink);
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .day-content { min-width: 0; }
  .day-ref {
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    margin: 0 0 .15rem;
    letter-spacing: -.1px;
  }
  .day-ref .day-tag {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: .68rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: var(--gold-deep);
    margin-right: .55rem;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  .day-focus {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: .96rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', serif;
  }

  .day-section { margin-top: .9rem; }
  .day-label {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: .7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 2.5px;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: .4rem;
  }
  .day-section ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    list-style: none;
  }
  .day-section ul li {
    margin-bottom: .35rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .day-section ul li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: -1.1rem;
    top: .65em;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    background: var(--gold);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  .day-section.pray p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.55;
    padding-left: .9rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--gold);
  }

  .check-btn {
    background: #fff;
    color: var(--muted);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: .45rem .85rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: .78rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transition: all .15s;
    letter-spacing: .2px;
  }
  .check-btn:hover {
    border-color: var(--ink);
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .day.complete .check-btn {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--gold);
    border-color: var(--ink);
  }

  footer {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: .82rem;
    padding: 2rem 1rem 3rem;
    font-style: italic;
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', serif;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .day {
      grid-template-columns: 32px 1fr;
      gap: .85rem;
      padding: 1.2rem 1rem;
    }
    .day.today { padding-left: calc(1rem - 3px); }
    .day-num { width: 30px; height: 30px; font-size: .82rem; }
    .check-btn { grid-column: 1 / -1; justify-self: end; margin-top: .25rem; }
    .week-header { padding: 1rem 1.1rem; }
    .week-title { font-size: 1.2rem; }
    main { padding: 1.5rem .9rem 3rem; }
    h1.title { font-size: 1.85rem; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header class="site">
  <p class="eyebrow">Home Church</p>
  <h1 class="title">The Life of David</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">A 20-week devotional walk through 1 &amp; 2 Samuel, 1 Chronicles, and the Psalms.</p>
  <div class="gold-rule"></div>
  <div class="progress-wrap">
    <div class="progress-text"><strong id="progress-count">0</strong> of 140 days complete</div>
    <div class="progress-bar"><div class="progress-fill" id="progress-fill"></div></div>
  </div>
</header>

<main>
  <div class="controls">
    <button class="primary" id="jump-today">Go to today</button>
    <button id="expand-all">Expand all</button>
    <button id="collapse-all">Collapse all</button>
    <div class="spacer"></div>
    <button class="ghost" id="reset-progress">Reset progress</button>
  </div>
  <div id="weeks-container"></div>
</main>

<footer>
  Walk slowly. Read prayerfully.
</footer>

<script>
const PLAN = [
  {
    week: 1,
    title: "The Need for a King",
    days: [
      { day: 1, ref: "1 Samuel 1", focus: "Hannah pours her heart out to God and doesn't dress it up.",
        reflect: ["Where are you putting on a brave face that God is actually inviting you to drop?", "When was the last time you let yourself really cry in prayer?"],
        pray: "God, I don't have to perform for you. Here's what's actually going on..." },
      { day: 2, ref: "1 Samuel 2", focus: "Hannah sings. Eli's sons treat the holy stuff like a perk.",
        reflect: ["Where has the holy stuff become routine for you?", "Has familiarity with church or the Bible dulled your wonder a little?"],
        pray: "Father, wake me back up. I don't want to be numb to who you are." },
      { day: 3, ref: "1 Samuel 3", focus: "God calls a kid in the dark. Samuel says, 'Speak, I'm listening.'",
        reflect: ["Are you actually listening for God, or just rehearsing what you want to say to Him?", "What would change if you started your day with 'Speak, Lord — I'm listening'?"],
        pray: "Speak, God. I'll stop talking long enough to actually hear you today." },
      { day: 4, ref: "1 Samuel 4", focus: "Israel grabs the ark like a good luck charm. It backfires.",
        reflect: ["Where are you using God instead of trusting Him?", "What's the thing you keep reaching for like it's going to fix you?"],
        pray: "Jesus, I don't want to use you. I want to know you. Show me where I've turned you into a tool." },
      { day: 5, ref: "1 Samuel 5–6", focus: "God doesn't need defending. He handles Himself among the Philistines.",
        reflect: ["Where do you feel like you have to protect God or argue Him into respectability?", "What does it free up to remember God can take care of His own reputation?"],
        pray: "God, you're not small. Forgive me for shrinking you. Show me your weight today." },
      { day: 6, ref: "1 Samuel 7–8", focus: "Israel wants a king like everybody else has.",
        reflect: ["Where in your life are you settling for what everyone else has instead of what God has for you?", "What 'kings' have you crowned that should've been God's seat?"],
        pray: "King Jesus, expose the lesser kings I keep crowning. Take the throne — for real this time." },
      { day: 7, ref: "1 Samuel 9–10", focus: "Saul gets anointed. Tall, handsome, looks like a king. Looks aren't the test.",
        reflect: ["Where are you measuring people (or yourself) by the outside?", "What does God see in you that nobody else does?"],
        pray: "God, I'm tired of being impressive. Make me actually faithful." }
    ]
  },
  {
    week: 2,
    title: "Saul's Rise & Fall",
    days: [
      { day: 8, ref: "1 Samuel 11–12", focus: "Saul leads a rescue; Samuel calls Israel to remember.",
        reflect: ["What victory in your life are you tempted to take credit for?", "How does remembering God's faithfulness reshape today's anxieties?"],
        pray: "Lord, I rehearse Your past kindness so that I can trust You with what's still ahead." },
      { day: 9, ref: "1 Samuel 13", focus: "Saul offers the sacrifice himself rather than wait.",
        reflect: ["Where is impatience pushing you to take a shortcut around obedience?", "What does it cost to wait on God when pressure mounts?"],
        pray: "Father, slow me down. Make me one who waits when waiting is what You ask." },
      { day: 10, ref: "1 Samuel 14", focus: "Jonathan trusts; Saul's rash vow nearly kills his son.",
        reflect: ["Compare Jonathan's faith with Saul's anxious leadership — what's the difference?", "Where is fear, not faith, driving your decisions right now?"],
        pray: "God, I want bold, simple faith like Jonathan's — believing nothing can hinder You from saving." },
      { day: 11, ref: "1 Samuel 15", focus: "Partial obedience is disobedience.",
        reflect: ["Where have you been calling 'good enough' what God called incomplete?", "What does it look like to obey fully today, not just mostly?"],
        pray: "Lord, search me for the things I've spared that You told me to surrender. I lay them down." },
      { day: 12, ref: "1 Samuel 16", focus: "God sees the heart; David is anointed.",
        reflect: ["How does it free you that 'the Lord looks on the heart'?", "What heart is God forming in you in the hidden field where no one is watching?"],
        pray: "Lord, You see me. Form in me a heart after Your own — even if no one notices but You." },
      { day: 13, ref: "1 Samuel 17", focus: "David and Goliath — God fights for His name.",
        reflect: ["What 'giant' is mocking the people of God in your life right now?", "Whose battle is it really? What changes when you remember that?"],
        pray: "The battle is Yours, Lord. Be glorified in what looks impossible to me today." },
      { day: 14, ref: "Psalm 8 & 19", focus: "God's glory in the heavens and in His Word.",
        reflect: ["Where can you see God's majesty in creation today?", "How does Scripture revive, rejoice, and warn you (Ps 19)?"],
        pray: "Heavens declare; Word revives. Open my eyes to Your glory written everywhere." }
    ]
  },
  {
    week: 3,
    title: "Favor & Jealousy",
    days: [
      { day: 15, ref: "1 Samuel 18", focus: "David's success stirs Saul's jealousy.",
        reflect: ["Where does someone else's blessing tempt you toward jealousy?", "How do you respond when God seems to favor another?"],
        pray: "Father, free me from comparison. Let me celebrate what You're doing in others." },
      { day: 16, ref: "1 Samuel 19", focus: "Saul tries to kill David; Michal and Jonathan protect him.",
        reflect: ["Have you been someone's Jonathan — protecting another person at cost to yourself?", "Where do you need God's protection right now?"],
        pray: "Lord, be my shield. And use me as a refuge for someone running for their life." },
      { day: 17, ref: "1 Samuel 20", focus: "Jonathan and David's covenant of friendship.",
        reflect: ["What does this kind of loyal friendship look like in your life?", "Who needs you to choose them this week, not just feel for them?"],
        pray: "Lord, give me one or two soul-friendships that strengthen me in You — and make me that for someone." },
      { day: 18, ref: "Psalm 59", focus: "David prays under Saul's surveillance.",
        reflect: ["What would you pray if your enemies were watching the door?", "How does naming threats before God lower their power?"],
        pray: "O my Strength, I will sing of Your steadfast love when the night comes." },
      { day: 19, ref: "Psalm 11", focus: "When the foundations are shaken, the Lord is in His holy temple.",
        reflect: ["What 'foundations' feel shaken in your life right now?", "How does the Lord's unshaken throne change your fear?"],
        pray: "Lord, You reign. I will not flee like a bird to the mountains — I take refuge in You." },
      { day: 20, ref: "Psalm 34", focus: "Taste and see — the Lord delivers from all fears.",
        reflect: ["What does it look like to 'magnify the Lord' today, even in trouble?", "Which fear do you need to bring to the One who hears?"],
        pray: "I sought the Lord, and He answered me. He is near to the brokenhearted — including mine." },
      { day: 21, ref: "Reflection & Prayer", focus: "Pause and pray over weeks 1–3.",
        reflect: ["Where has God been forming you in the past three weeks?", "Where is jealousy, fear, or impatience still ruling? What needs to be confessed?"],
        pray: "Lord, You are forming me. I yield. Carry forward what You've started in me." }
    ]
  },
  {
    week: 4,
    title: "Into the Wilderness",
    days: [
      { day: 22, ref: "1 Samuel 21", focus: "David flees to Nob and to Achish.",
        reflect: ["What does desperation tempt you to do that you wouldn't normally do?", "When God's calling has been delayed, where does your trust drift?"],
        pray: "Father, in the in-between, keep me honest. Don't let fear write my next move." },
      { day: 23, ref: "1 Samuel 22", focus: "The cave of Adullam; the priests of Nob slain.",
        reflect: ["Who are the 'distressed, in debt, discontented' that God might be sending to you?", "What grief do you carry from collateral damage in others' choices?"],
        pray: "Lord, let me be a cave of refuge for the weary. And carry the sorrow my decisions caused." },
      { day: 24, ref: "1 Samuel 23", focus: "David inquires of the Lord — repeatedly.",
        reflect: ["When was the last time you asked God before deciding?", "What does it mean to inquire of the Lord, not just inform Him?"],
        pray: "Speak before I move. Lead before I act. I will inquire of You, Lord." },
      { day: 25, ref: "1 Samuel 24", focus: "David spares Saul in the cave.",
        reflect: ["Where do you have a chance to repay evil with restraint?", "How does trusting God's timing change how you treat people who've hurt you?"],
        pray: "Lord, I refuse to take vengeance with my own hand. You are the just Judge." },
      { day: 26, ref: "Psalm 52", focus: "The boastful man and the green olive tree.",
        reflect: ["Where are you tempted to trust in 'abundance of riches' or strength of self?", "What does it look like to be a 'green olive tree in the house of God'?"],
        pray: "I trust in the steadfast love of God forever. Root me in Your house, not in my résumé." },
      { day: 27, ref: "Psalm 57", focus: "In the shadow of Your wings I will take refuge.",
        reflect: ["What 'shadow of Your wings' feels real to you today?", "Can you sing — really sing — even before the deliverance comes?"],
        pray: "Awake, my soul! I will sing to You among the nations, even in the cave." },
      { day: 28, ref: "Psalm 142", focus: "I cry out — no one cares for my soul.",
        reflect: ["When has loneliness driven you to God in a new way?", "What does it mean to 'pour out your complaint before Him'?"],
        pray: "You know my way. You are my refuge, my portion in the land of the living." }
    ]
  },
  {
    week: 5,
    title: "Formed in the Cave",
    days: [
      { day: 29, ref: "Psalm 7", focus: "Plea for vindication; God as righteous judge.",
        reflect: ["Where do you need God to vindicate you instead of defending yourself?", "How does trust in God as judge free you from anxious self-defense?"],
        pray: "O Lord my God, in You I take refuge. Save me, and let me leave the verdict to You." },
      { day: 30, ref: "Psalm 27", focus: "The Lord is my light and my salvation — whom shall I fear?",
        reflect: ["What 'one thing' have you asked of the Lord lately?", "Where is fear lying to you about who God is?"],
        pray: "I will see the goodness of the Lord in the land of the living. Wait for the Lord — be strong." },
      { day: 31, ref: "Psalm 31", focus: "Into Your hand I commit my spirit.",
        reflect: ["What feels too heavy to hold today?", "How is God a 'rock of refuge' specifically for you in this season?"],
        pray: "Into Your hand I commit my spirit. My times are in Your hands." },
      { day: 32, ref: "Psalm 56", focus: "When I am afraid, I put my trust in You.",
        reflect: ["What's beneath your fear right now — what do you really believe about God?", "Are your tears in God's bottle, or are they drying alone?"],
        pray: "Lord, You keep count of my tossings. In God I trust; what can flesh do to me?" },
      { day: 33, ref: "Psalm 140–141", focus: "Deliver me from evil; set a guard over my mouth.",
        reflect: ["What words have escaped you this week that need confession?", "Where do you need God's protection from your own appetites?"],
        pray: "Set a guard, O Lord, over my mouth — and over my heart, where the words begin." },
      { day: 34, ref: "Psalm 120", focus: "Too long have I had my dwelling among those who hate peace.",
        reflect: ["Where do you live among people who 'hate peace'? How does that wear on you?", "What does it mean to be 'for peace' when others are not?"],
        pray: "Lord, when I'm surrounded by hostility, keep me a person of peace — anchored in You." },
      { day: 35, ref: "Reflection", focus: "What is God forming in you in the cave?",
        reflect: ["David's psalms in this season are remarkably honest. What does that invite from you?", "What kind of person is God making you when no one is watching?"],
        pray: "Form me, Lord. Don't waste this hidden season. Make me Yours all the way through." }
    ]
  },
  {
    week: 6,
    title: "Integrity Under Pressure",
    days: [
      { day: 36, ref: "1 Samuel 25", focus: "Nabal, Abigail, and David's near-vengeance.",
        reflect: ["Where is your anger close to making a permanent decision?", "Has someone been an Abigail to you — interrupting your worst self?"],
        pray: "Lord, send Abigails. And keep me from acting in heat what I'd regret in calm." },
      { day: 37, ref: "1 Samuel 26", focus: "David spares Saul again.",
        reflect: ["How is restraint a form of worship?", "Where is God testing what you do with power you didn't have to use?"],
        pray: "Father, I will not stretch my hand against what You've called me to leave to You." },
      { day: 38, ref: "1 Samuel 27", focus: "David lives among the Philistines — the gray seasons.",
        reflect: ["What do you do in the long, in-between seasons that don't feel triumphant?", "Where might you be drifting because the wait is long?"],
        pray: "Lord, even in the gray, hold me. Don't let me settle for less than what You've promised." },
      { day: 39, ref: "Psalm 17", focus: "Hide me in the shadow of Your wings.",
        reflect: ["What would change if your prayer was, 'Try me, You will find nothing'?", "Where do you most need to be hidden in God right now?"],
        pray: "Keep me as the apple of Your eye; hide me in the shadow of Your wings." },
      { day: 40, ref: "Psalm 35", focus: "Contend, O Lord, with those who contend with me.",
        reflect: ["What does it look like to bring conflict to God before to people?", "How do you honor God when people repay your good with evil?"],
        pray: "Lord, You are my advocate. I lay down my own defense and trust You." },
      { day: 41, ref: "Psalm 54", focus: "Behold, God is my helper.",
        reflect: ["When have you been 'sold out' or betrayed? What did you learn about God there?", "What does it mean today that God is your upholder?"],
        pray: "Behold, God is my helper; the Lord is the upholder of my life." },
      { day: 42, ref: "Psalm 63", focus: "My soul thirsts for You.",
        reflect: ["Where in your life are you most thirsty?", "What would it look like to meditate on God 'in the watches of the night'?"],
